  "prompt": "How much does it cost to buy a flight simulator?",
  "response": "The cost of a flight simulator can vary widely depending on several factors, including the type of simulator, its complexity, and the intended use (e.g., personal use, professional training, or academic purposes). Here are some general categories and their price ranges:\n\n1. **Consumer Flight Simulators**:\n   - **Software**: Flight simulation software like Microsoft Flight Simulator or X-Plane can cost between $60 to $100.\n   - **Hardware**: Basic setups with joysticks or yokes can range from $50 to $500. More advanced setups with multiple monitors and additional peripherals can cost $1,000 or more.\n\n2. **Professional/Commercial Flight Simulators**:\n   - These high-fidelity simulators used for pilot training can cost anywhere from $50,000 to several million dollars. Full-motion simulators with sophisticated systems may range from $1 million to over $10 million.\n\n3. **Home Simulators**:\n   - Mid-range home simulators, which may include higher-quality hardware and software, can cost between $1,000 to $10,000, depending on the setup.\n\n4. **DIY Simulators**:\n   - If you're building your own setup, costs can vary based on the components you choose, but a decent DIY flight simulator can be built for anywhere between $500 and $5,000.\n\nOverall, the cost can be as low as a few hundred dollars for a basic setup to millions for high-end, professional training systems.",
